84. Implement a PHP program that creates sessions, sets values in sessions, and removes data from
the sessions.
code:
<?php
session_start(); // Start the session

// Set session variables
$_SESSION["username"] = "Keerthana";
$_SESSION["role"] = "Admin";

echo "<h3>Session Created and Values Set</h3>";
echo "Username: " . $_SESSION["username"] . "<br>";
echo "Role: " . $_SESSION["role"] . "<br>";

// Remove a specific session variable
unset($_SESSION["role"]);
echo "<br><b>After unsetting 'role':</b><br>";
if (isset($_SESSION["role"])) {
    echo "Role: " . $_SESSION["role"];
} else {
    echo "Role has been removed.<br>";
}

// Destroy all session data
session_destroy();
echo "<br><b>Session destroyed. All data removed.</b>";
?>
